{"title_page": "Shakir Shuja Abadi", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name                = Shakir Shujabadi\n| image               = \n| birth_place         = \n| birth_date          = 1953 or 1954<ref name=\"tribune.com.pk\"/>\n| citizenship         = [[Pakistani]] \n| known_for           = [[Poetry]]\n| spouse              =Shabnam Shakir\n| children            =\n}}\n'''Shakir Shujabadi'''  is a prominent [[Saraiki people|Saraiki]]-language poet. <ref name=\"tribune.com.pk\">{{cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/655569/godfather-of-seraiki-poetry-searching-for-Muhammad-Farhad-Malik/|title=Godfather of Seraiki romance: Searching for Muhammad Farhad Malik - The Express Tribune|date=6 January 2014|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"tribune.com.pk1\">{{cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1368097/king-seraiki-poetry-receives-presidential-award-second-time/|title=King of Seraiki romance receives presidential award for second time - The Express Tribune|date=29 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nation.com.pk/national/11-Jan-2016/book-launched|title=Book launched|publisher=}}</ref> In 2007, he received his first presidential award.<ref name=\"tribune.com.pk1\"/> In 2017, he received his second presidential award.<ref name=\"tribune.com.pk1\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://pakobserver.net/governor-confers-awards-on-23-personalities-on-pakistan-day/|title=Governor confers awards on 23 personalities on Pakistan Day - PakObserver|first=|last=Webmaster|date=24 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref> His first proper [[Mushaira]] was held in 1986.<ref name=\"tribune.com.pk\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.shakirshujaabadi.com Shakir Shuja Abadi]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shuj Abadi, Shakir}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n[[Category:Pakistani people with disabilities]]\n[[Category:Saraiki-language poets]]\n[[Category:Saraiki people]]\n\n\n{{Pakistan-bio-stub}} \nSome versus of s